{"concept_id": "concept_business_understandability", "canonical_label_en": "Business Understandability", "canonical_label_zh": "能力圈", "definition": "Whether the business model is simple, predictable, and within Buffett's circle of competence. Buffett avoids businesses he cannot understand, regardless of how attractive the numbers look.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_quality", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_durable_competitive_advantage", "canonical_label_en": "Durable Competitive Advantage", "canonical_label_zh": "竞争性护城河", "definition": "The 'economic moat' — structural advantages that protect the business from competition for decades. This is the single most important qualitative factor in Buffett's framework. He looks for businesses where competitive position widens over time rather than erodes.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_moat", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_pricing_power", "canonical_label_en": "Pricing Power", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "The ability to raise prices without losing customers — Buffett considers this the single best test of whether a business has a moat. He told the Financial Crisis Inquiry Commission in 2010 that pricing power is more important than good management.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_moat", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_return_on_equity_without_leverage", "canonical_label_en": "Return On Equity Without Leverage", "canonical_label_zh": "商业质量", "definition": "Consistently high returns on equity achieved without excessive debt. Buffett focuses on ROE as the primary measure of management's effectiveness at deploying shareholder capital, but insists it must be earned with conservative capital structures.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_quality", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_management_integrity_and_candor", "canonical_label_en": "Management Integrity And Candor", "canonical_label_zh": "会计质量", "definition": "Buffett demands management that is honest, shareholder-oriented, and candid about both successes and failures. He values managers who think like owners and resist the institutional imperative to waste capital.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_management", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_owner_earnings_and_cash_generation", "canonical_label_en": "Owner Earnings And Cash Generation", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Buffett's concept of 'owner earnings' — net income plus depreciation and amortization, minus required capital expenditures to maintain competitive position. This reflects the true cash a business generates for its owners, and Buffett prefers businesses where owner earnings closely track or exceed reported earnings.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_quality", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_margin_of_safety", "canonical_label_en": "Margin Of Safety", "canonical_label_zh": "估值", "definition": "Buying at a price significantly below estimated intrinsic value to protect against analytical errors and unforeseen events. Buffett inherited this concept directly from Benjamin Graham and considers it the cornerstone of intelligent investing.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_valuation", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_capital_allocation_track_record", "canonical_label_en": "Capital Allocation Track Record", "canonical_label_zh": "资本配置", "definition": "How management deploys the cash the business generates. Buffett considers capital allocation the CEO's most important job and evaluates whether retained earnings have created at least one dollar of market value for each dollar retained.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_management", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_financial_strength_and_conservatism", "canonical_label_en": "Financial Strength And Conservatism", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Buffett insists on strong balance sheets with conservative leverage. He views debt as dangerous because it can turn a temporary business setback into a permanent capital loss. He famously said you only find out who is swimming naked when the tide goes out.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_risk", "source_lineage": "buffett.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["buffett"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_inversion_stress_test", "canonical_label_en": "Inversion Stress Test", "canonical_label_zh": "反向思考", "definition": "Before analyzing why an investment might work, systematically enumerate every way it could fail. Only investments that survive aggressive inversion deserve further analysis.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_inversion", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_psychological_bias_audit", "canonical_label_en": "Psychological Bias Audit", "canonical_label_zh": "行为金融", "definition": "Systematically check whether the investment thesis is contaminated by cognitive biases from Munger's 25 Standard Causes of Human Misjudgment. The analyst's own psychology is the greatest source of error.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_psychology", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_competitive_moat_durability", "canonical_label_en": "Competitive Moat Durability", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Assess whether the competitive advantage is structurally durable or merely cyclical. Munger emphasized that moats erode by default and only survive when reinforced by economics, not just management effort.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_moat", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_management_integrity_and_incentives", "canonical_label_en": "Management Integrity And Incentives", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Munger's first question about management is not 'Are they talented?' but 'Are their incentives aligned and are they honest?' He believed incentive-caused bias is the most powerful force in business and that talented but misaligned managers destroy value reliably.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_management", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_multidisciplinary_model_check", "canonical_label_en": "Multidisciplinary Model Check", "canonical_label_zh": "思维模型", "definition": "Apply models from outside finance — biology, physics, psychology, mathematics — to test whether the investment thesis holds under different analytical lenses. If the thesis only works through a financial lens, it is likely incomplete.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_multidisciplinary", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_lollapalooza_effect_detection", "canonical_label_en": "Lollapalooza Effect Detection", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Identify whether multiple psychological tendencies or economic forces are combining to create an extreme outcome — either extremely positive (Costco's flywheel) or extremely negative (Enron's fraud). Munger coined 'lollapalooza' for cases where 3+ forces compound in the same direction.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_psychology", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_simplicity_and_understandability", "canonical_label_en": "Simplicity And Understandability", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Munger insisted that if you cannot explain the investment thesis in a few sentences to a reasonably intelligent person, you do not understand it well enough. Complexity is the enemy of good judgment. This differs from Buffett's version — Munger specifically distrusted financial complexity and leverage.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_multidisciplinary", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_margin_of_safety_through_quality", "canonical_label_en": "Margin Of Safety Through Quality", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "Munger evolved Buffett's thinking from 'buy fair businesses at wonderful prices' to 'buy wonderful businesses at fair prices.' His margin of safety comes not from statistical cheapness but from business quality so high that even overpaying somewhat still produces excellent long-term returns.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_moat", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_opportunity_cost_discipline", "canonical_label_en": "Opportunity Cost Discipline", "canonical_label_zh": "集中投资", "definition": "Every investment must be compared against the best available alternative, not just evaluated in isolation. Munger was ruthless about opportunity cost — a merely good investment is a bad investment if a great one is available.", "parent_concept": "concept_category_inversion", "source_lineage": "munger.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["munger"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_商业模式简洁性", "canonical_label_en": "商业模式简洁性", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "商业模式必须简单到一句话能说清楚。如果需要复杂的解释才能理解公司怎么赚钱，那就不是好的投资标的。好的生意模式是'傻瓜都能经营'的生意。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_model", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_企业文化/本分", "canonical_label_en": "企业文化/本分", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "企业文化是我最看重的东西，甚至超过商业模式。本分意味着做对的事情，不占别人便宜，诚信经营。没有好的企业文化，再好的商业模式最终都会出问题。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_benfen", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_消费者心智", "canonical_label_en": "消费者心智", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "一个品牌在消费者心智中的位置决定了它的长期竞争力。消费者想到某个品类时第一个想到的品牌，就拥有最强的护城河。这种心智份额一旦建立，竞争对手很难撼动。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_model", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_管理层诚信与能力", "canonical_label_en": "管理层诚信与能力", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "管理层必须是诚实、能干、有企业家精神的人。我宁可投一个一流管理层经营的二流生意，也不投二流管理层经营的一流生意。管理层是否本分，是否把股东利益放在心上，比任何财务指标都重要。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_management", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_长期竞争优势/护城河", "canonical_label_en": "长期竞争优势/护城河", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "企业必须有持续的竞争优势，让竞争对手即使知道你怎么做也无法复制。护城河可以来自品牌、规模、网络效应、转换成本等，但必须是真实的、可持续的，而不是靠烧钱或补贴维持的。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_model", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_安全边际", "canonical_label_en": "安全边际", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "好公司也需要好价格。安全边际不是精确计算出来的，而是一种模糊的正确。如果一眼看上去就是便宜的，那就是有安全边际；如果需要反复计算才能得出'便宜'的结论，那就没有足够的安全边际。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_valuation", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_产品力与用户体验", "canonical_label_en": "产品力与用户体验", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "产品本身是否优秀，用户体验是否出色。作为消费电子行业出身的人，我深知产品力是一切的基础。一个真正好的产品，用户用了就离不开，这是最强的护城河。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_model", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_财务健康度", "canonical_label_en": "财务健康度", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "虽然我不喜欢复杂的财务分析，但基本的财务健康是底线。不能有太多负债，现金流必须健康，ROE要够高。这些是最基本的要求，不需要深入分析，一眼就能看出来。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_valuation", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
{"concept_id": "concept_商业生态位", "canonical_label_en": "商业生态位", "canonical_label_zh": "", "definition": "公司在产业链中处于什么位置，是否有话语权。最好的生意是消费者和供应商都离不开你的生意。如果你只是产业链中可替代的一环，那就不是好生意。", "parent_concept": "concept_category_business_model", "source_lineage": "duan.json profile factor", "decision_factor_for": ["duan"], "introduced_at": "2026-04-19T14:06:42.124485+00:00", "status": "active"}
